nl.tue.geometrycore.algorithms.mst

Class MinimumSpanningTree<TGraph extends SimpleGraph<TGeom,TVertex,TEdge>,TGeom extends OrientedGeometry<TGeom>,TVertex extends SimpleVertex<TGeom,TVertex,TEdge>,TEdge extends SimpleEdge<TGeom,TVertex,TEdge>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.tue.geometrycore.algorithms.mst.MinimumSpanningTree<TGraph,TGeom,TVertex,TEdge>
  • Type Parameters:
    TGraph - Class of graph to be used for spanning-tree computations
    TGeom - Class of edge geometry used by TGraph
    TVertex - Class of vertex used by TGraph
    TEdge - Class of edge used by TGraph

    public class MinimumSpanningTree<TGraph extends SimpleGraph<TGeom,TVertex,TEdge>,TGeom extends OrientedGeometry<TGeom>,TVertex extends SimpleVertex<TGeom,TVertex,TEdge>,TEdge extends SimpleEdge<TGeom,TVertex,TEdge>>
extends java.lang.Object
    Implementation of Prim's minimum spanning tree algorithm, running in O(V + E log V) time. Note that an instance of this class assumes the vertices of the graph do not change. If the graph is changed, create a fresh instance for new spanning-tree queries.
